# ---------------------------------------------------------
# EMERGENCY STOP SITUATIONS
# ---------------------------------------------------------

**STOP immediately and ask if:**
- User requests emojis in visible content
- User insists on "24/7" or specific numbers
- User wants pricing amounts (FJD, USD, $)
- User requests features that break compliance
- User asks to mention "Book now" or booking features (Phase 2)
- User wants "Pay with card" or digital payment mentions (cash only)
- User requests "Login" or "Sign up" functionality (Phase 2)
- User wants "Download app" CTAs (apps not built yet)
- User asks to mention "Real-time tracking" (Phase 2)
- User wants native app features mentioned (Phase 3)
- Multiple conflicting instructions
- Unclear about which hero image to use
- Logo changes requested without approval

**RESPONSE TEMPLATE FOR PHASE VIOLATIONS:**
```
‚ö†Ô∏è PHASE 1 SCOPE VIOLATION

Requested: [feature/content user asked for]
Issue: This is a Phase 2/3 feature, not built yet

Current Phase: Phase 1 (Marketing Website Only)
Feature Available In: Phase 2 (Booking Platform) or Phase 3 (Mobile Apps)

Approved Alternatives:
A) Use "Get started" CTA ‚Üí leads to contact form
B) Use "Coming soon" language
C) Add to "Future features" section (if approved by client)

Would you like to proceed with an alternative?
```


